node.text:
Floating mountain house ✨ #archoskar
The 'Casa 1510' (450 m²).
Designed by NordE/t Arquitectura (@nordest_arquitectura, 2018).
Located in Aigua Blava, Begur, Spain.
Photos by Adria Goula Photo (@adriagoulaphoto).
.
"Over every mountain there is a path, although it may not be seen from the valley." — Theodore Roethke. #architectureoskar
.
The House is understood as a floating volume on the mountain. A space for contemplation that it’s opened to the views and to the garden simultaneously. The building is integrated to the landscape reducing its presence just to a concrete volume. The other elements are materialized with natural stone from the site, in that way, they can be read like if they come out from the land.
.
#floating #mountain #casa #spain

node.text:
Analog-digital clock art ✨ #archoskar
The 'A million Times 96'.
Created by Humans since 1982 (@humanssince1982) from Stockholm, Sweden.
Located in Chelsea, New York City, New York, USA.
Video & description by Humans since 1982.
Song by Stromae, 'Alors On Danse'.
.
"The time you enjoy wasting is not wasted time." — Bertrand Russell. #architectureoskar
.
'A million Times' is an ongoing project by Humans since 1982 that continues the conceptual exploration of one of their first collaborative projects The ClockClock (2008) to create kinetic sculptures that present clocks as art objects, unleashed from a solely pragmatic existence. The hands of multiple analogue clocks display the time in a digital format every minute, between which they are programmed to perform abstract, dance-like choreographies.
.
#time #art #analog #digital

node.text:
Architectural details ✨ #archoskar
The 'Loggia di Davide at Fondazione Palazzo Te' (@fondazionepalazzote).
Designed by Giulio Romano (1535).
Located in Mantova, Lombardy, Italy.
Video by Nicole Marzari (@humanaee).
Description by Fondazione Palazzo Te.
.
"Architecture should speak of its time and place, but yearn for timelessness." — Frank Gehry. #architectureoskar
.
The Loggia owes its name to the decorations related to the Stories of David, frescoed in the lunettes and in the vaulted ceiling. The large porch well sums up the life in the villa, opening onto the Courtyard of Honour with a central arch and towards the fish ponds and garden, once full of flowers and plants, with three arches supported by groups of four columns.
.
#architecture #italia #mantova #palazzo

node.text:
Mountainside ride 💦 #archoskar
The 'Parque de Atracciones Monte Igueldo' ('Mount Igueldo Amusement Park').
Located in Donostia-San Sebastian, Spain.
Video Beatriz Alemán (@beaa.alem).
Song by The Macarons Project, 'Moon River'.
Description by Monte Igueldo.
.
"You cannot step into the same river twice." — Heraclitus. #architectureoskar
.
Inaugurated in 1911, Monte Igueldo has slowly but unstoppably morphed into the attraction that everyone knows in Donostia, combining tradition and modernity, the original attractions coexist with new ones. Monte Igueldo is an emblematic place for the people of San Sebastian and an unforgettable experience for the ones visiting it for the first time.
.
#mountain #rollercoaster #river #spain

node.text:
Law library in München 📚 #archoskar
The 'Juristische Bibliothek'.
Designed by Georg von Hauberrisser (1906).
Located in München, Germany.
Video by Madeline Lu (@lumadeline).
Song by Soundtrack Orchestra, 'Hedwig's Theme (From the Movie "Harry Potter")'.
.
"At his best, man is the noblest of all animals; separated from law and justice he is the worst." — Aristotle. #architectureoskar
.
#law #library #münchen #germany
